 England":"Icklingham, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Melton, Suffolk, England":"Melton, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Melton Constable, Norfolk, England":"Melton Constable, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1408–1473":"1408–1473","1400–1465":"1400–1465","1429–1487":"1429–1487","1430–1497":"1430–1497","1433–Female":"1433–Deceased","1384–1423":"1384–1423","1390–1456":"1390–1456","1473":"1473","1384":"1384","Abt 1423":"about 1423","1390":"1390","1424":"1424","about 1429":"about 1429","1456":"1456","1423":"1423","1433":"1433","Abt 1465":"about 1465","1400":"1400","1487":"1487","1465":"1465","1497":"1497","1430":"1430","1408":"1408","about 1430":"about 1430","1429":"1429","Lackford, Suffolk, England":"Lackford, Suffolk, England","Kirkby Stephen, Westmorland, England":"Kirkby Stephen, Westmorland, England","Icklingham, Suffolk, England":"Icklingham, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Melton, Suffolk, England":"Melton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Melton Constable, Norfolk, England":"Melton Constable, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Astley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of several places in England called Astley (in Lancashire, Shropshire, Warwickshire, Worcestershire, and Yorkshire), from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. The modern surname seems to be particularly associated with the one in Warwickshire. See also   Astle  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Astle","meanings":["English: habitational name from a place in Cheshire called Astle, from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’. There may also have been some confusion with <i>Asthall</i> and   Astley  . Or occasionally this may be a topographic name denoting residence on an ‘east hill’ (from Middle English <i>ast</i> + <i>hill</i> or <i>hull</i>), i.e. a hill to the east of a settlement.","English: perhaps also a habitational name from Astwell, Northamptonshire, from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>wielle</i> ‘spring’.","English: habitational name from Asthall, Oxfordshire, from Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>halh</i> ‘nook’."]}]},{"name":"Anna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[{"name":"Anne","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Anna Astley was born in 1408, in Melton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, her father, Sir Thomas Astley III, was 25 and her mother, Elizabeth Dacre, was 18. She married Thomas Gedding in 1424, in Lackford, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died in 1473, at the age of 65."},"et":{"1408–1473":"1408–1473","1400–1465":"1400–1465","1429–1487":"1429–1487","1430–1497":"1430–1497","1433–Female":"1433–Surnud","1384–1423":"1384–1423","1390–1456":"1390–1456","1473":"1473","1384":"1384","Abt 1423":"umbes 1423","1390":"1390","1424":"1424","about 1429":"umbes 1429","1456":"1456